## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of transport in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Transport is the bounded movement structure
through which actors,
items,
vehicles,
and carried resources
move between valid locations and states.

## architectural_position
Transport sits between:
- map/time coordinates
- housing/location presence
- item/inventory movement
- work/trade execution
- nation/world boundary crossing

## required_behavior
- transport context must remain explicit
- route/origin/destination basis must remain explicit
- current and historical transport states must remain distinguishable
- carried subject scope must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- route intent does not imply completed arrival
- movement visibility must not overwrite location truth
- ambiguous transport scope fails closed

## state_model
The transport domain distinguishes:
- planned transport
- active transport
- delayed/restricted transport
- completed transport
- historical transport

## review_checklist
- route basis is explicit
- carried subject scope is explicit
- completion meaning is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
